	<texts id="2001">
		<paragraph indent="0" tabs="" style="normal" height="0" width="400" y="+6" x="12" type="text"><![CDATA[<TEXTFORMAT LEADING="2"><P ALIGN="LEFT"><FONT FACE="Verdana" SIZE="13" COLOR="#000000" LETTERSPACING="0" KERNING="0">It is very important to write a good introductory paragraph for your composition. If your introduction is good, it makes the rest of the composition easier to write and it makes a good impression on the reader. Remember, if you decide not to write a balanced 'for and against' composition, you should give your personal opinion in the first paragraph and repeat it in the conclusion.</FONT></P></TEXTFORMAT>]]></paragraph>
